1) It would rather detract from the professionalism of the Foundation, wouldn't it?

2) I suppose, if it's trying to make fan-fiction out of XML or HTML or whatever, it might cause problems. (That would be interesting to see…)

If you're talking about our recent visitor, I think this SCP is too random for that sort of thing. Consider how scattered the interpolations of 732 are compared to the invariance of that "HAGGER" entity.

As a side note, once a record is completely corrupted, it seems to be edited for consistency and relevance by some force, 732 or otherwise. After all, 732 would not last long (and be as much trouble) if it could not blend in, and making its "victims" look genuine is a part of that. Some are remarkably convincing…





